cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a method for localizing chest disease in medical images using unsupervised and weakly supervised models. This task falls under computer vision and machine learning, which are covered by the arXiv CS sub-categories cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE. Given that the paper focuses on deep learning-based solutions for medical image analysis, cs.CV is the most likely sub-category. The use of unsupervised and weakly supervised models also suggests cs.LG and cs.AI as likely sub-categories. The use of attention maps and region proposals suggests cs.MM as a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of a learned spatial masking mechanism suggests cs.NE as a possible sub-category.
